<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/12570a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-19T16:00:00-05:00">December 19, 1918—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Press reports give summary of recent statement alleged to have been made
                            by Okuma, indicating Japan’s ambitions in South Sea Islands. Please
                            cable substance of statement, indicating reason for <pb facs="0563" n="493" xml:id="pg_493"/> statement, date, occasion upon which made,
                            and such other information as you may be able to obtain. Please mail
                            full text in first pouch.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>